Syntax and Operational Semantics
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The syntax and operational semantics of Pony is presented here as a small-step
 operational semantics that expresses a simplified subset of the full Pony
 language.
 In this subset, tuples are modelled as classes, whereas in the full language
 they are not.
 In addition, control structures such as conditional, loops, and exception
 handling, have been not been covered in this semantics, nor have the semantics
 of boolean and machine word types been addressed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In addition, the full language has 
\emph on
primitive 
\emph default
types (stateless singleton types similar to parameterised modules), 
\emph on
struct 
\emph default
types for C ABI compatibility, single-assignment fields and variables, embedded
 fields, nominal and structural subtyping, intersection and union types,
 object literals, lambdas, partial application, pattern matching, case functions
, and most importantly generic types and methods.
 Various forms of syntactic sugar are also used to allow for more succinct
 code.
\end_layout

